# Critical invariants — ticketing (NixOS flake)

## Commits (STRICT)
- NEVER auto-commit — only commit on explicit user request ("commit", "committe das")
- NEVER skip hooks (`--no-verify`)
- NEVER force-push to main/master or tags

## Releases / tags
- If this repo uses tags for deploys, NEVER force-push tags
- Prefer release scripts (if present) over manual version bumps for production releases

## Security
- Secrets: edit encrypted `secrets/secrets.yaml` with `sops` only; never commit plaintext. Runtime via sops-nix (e.g. `/run/secrets/…`).
- Do not read `.env`, `.env.*`, credential, token, or private-key files unless the user explicitly asks for a specific value or line
- Never commit `.env` files or credentials
- If any client-side code exists in the tree: never ship secrets into the client bundle

## NixOS / this flake
- Festival-specific services use the option namespace `zugvoegel.services.<name>` (see `modules/*/default.nix`)
- New module: add `modules/<name>/default.nix` — picked up automatically by `flake.nix` (`readDir ./modules`)
